IO-HTML version 0.02, released January 29, 2012


This module opens a file and performs automatic charset detection
based on the HTML5 algorithm.  You can then pass the filehandle to
HTML::Parser or a related module (or just read it yourself).



INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install



DEPENDENCIES

  Package   Minimum Version
  --------- ---------------
  perl       5.008
  Carp       
  Encode     
  Exporter   5.57



CHANGES
    Here's what's new in version 0.02 of IO-HTML:
    (See the file "Changes" for the full revision history.)

	- Fix 20-open.t to work on OpenBSD & Solaris
	  (It seems they don't like <:raw on in-memory files.)



